    "output": "{\"content\": \"{\\n  \\\"status_reasoning\\\": {\\n    \\\"determined_status\\\": \\\"healthy\\\",\\n    \\\"status_justification\\\": [\\n      \\\"All 16 pods in namespace sock-shop are in Running status with 0 restarts.\\\",\\n      \\\"Kubernetes events show only normal lifecycle activity; the few Unhealthy events for carts startup probe are historical and the pod is now Running.\\\",\\n      \\\"No evidence of current errors, CrashLoopBackOff, or pending/failed pods.\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"data_quality\\\": {\\n      \\\"completeness\\\": \\\"partial\\\",\\n      \\\"gaps\\\": [\\n        \\\"metrics_unavailable\\\",\\n        \\\"events_truncated\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"confidence_impact\\\": \\\"Health score slightly reduced due to lack of live CPU/memory metrics and truncated events, but pod and event data are strong indicators of good health.\\\"\\n    }\\n  },\\n  \\\"thoughts\\\": {\\n    \\\"key_observations\\\": [\\n      \\\"Pod inventory for sock-shop shows 16 pods, all Ready and Running, including application components (carts, catalogue, orders, payment, shipping, user, their DBs, queue-master, rabbitmq, front-end) plus flash-agent and MCP-related pods.\\\",\\n      \\\"All pods report 0 restarts, suggesting stable workloads since deployment.\\\",\\n      \\\"Events include normal scheduling, image pull, container creation/started messages, and a couple of transient Unhealthy startup probe failures for carts, which have since cleared.\\\",\\n      \\\"A flash-agent pod (app=flash-agent) is present, likely a test/chaos/agent framework, but there are no events indicating active chaos or fault injection.\\\",\\n      \\\"Attempt to fetch pod resource metrics via pods_top failed due to RBAC (metrics.k8s.io forbidden for the MCP service account).\\\",\\n      \\\"Attempt to list Prometheus metrics via list_metrics failed because that tool is not available in this MCP setup.\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"analysis_approach\\\": [\\n      \\\"Li